The issue with the code is that the `Iterator` is not being used correctly in the `doBattle()` method of the `GangWar` class. Instead of using `Iterator.next()` to get the next `ComparableGang` from the `gangs` set, the code is using `gangs.iterator()` which returns an iterator for the `gangs` set. This means that the `Iterator` is not guaranteed to return the next `ComparableGang` in the order of the set.

To fix this issue, the code should use `Iterator.next()` to get the next `ComparableGang` from the `gangs` set, like this:
```scss
while (gangs.size() > 1) {
    Iterator<ComparableGang> i = gangs.iterator();
    ComparableGang g1 = i.next();
    ComparableGang g2 = i.next();
    System.out.println(g1.getName() + " attacks " + g2.getName());
    g1.attack(g2);
    if (g2.getStrength() == 0) {
        System.out.println(g1.getName() + " smokes " + g2.getName());
        gangs.remove(g2);
    }
    if (g1.getStrength() == 0) {
        System.out.println(g2.getName() + " repels " + g1.getName());
        gangs.remove(g1);
    }
}
```
This will ensure that the `Iterator` is used correctly and the next `ComparableGang` in the order of the set is retrieved.
